---
export const prerender = true;

import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import InflationCalculator from '../../components/tools/InflationCalculator';

const title = 'Pakistan Inflation Impact Calculator — Purchasing Power 2015–2026';
const description =
  'Calculate how inflation has eroded purchasing power in Pakistan from 2015 to 2026 using PBS Consumer Price Index data. Includes year-on-year inflation bar chart.';
const pageUrl = 'https://hisaabkar.pk/tools/pakistan-inflation-calculator';
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'WebApplication',
    name: title,
    description,
    url: pageUrl,
    applicationCategory: 'FinanceApplication',
    operatingSystem: 'Web, Android, iOS',
    offers: { '@type': 'Offer', price: '0', priceCurrency: 'PKR' },
    featureList: 'PBS CPI data 2015-2026, Year-on-year inflation chart, Purchasing power erosion calculator, Official government data source',
    inLanguage: 'en-PK',
    publisher: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'HisaabKar.pk', url: 'https://hisaabkar.pk' },
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://hisaabkar.pk' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Tools', item: 'https://hisaabkar.pk/tools' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: 'Inflation Calculator', item: pageUrl },
    ],
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'FAQPage',
    mainEntity: [
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'What is Pakistan\'s inflation rate in 2026?',
        acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Pakistan\'s CPI inflation has significantly declined from its peak of 38% in May 2023 to approximately 0.3-0.7% YoY in early 2026, the lowest in years. This steep decline reflects the impact of the IMF stabilisation program, tight monetary policy (policy rate held at 22% through 2023-24), improved supply chains, and base effect. However, cumulative inflation since 2020 remains very high, meaning prices are still far above pre-crisis levels.' },
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'What does the PBS CPI measure in Pakistan?',
        acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'The Pakistan Bureau of Statistics (PBS) Consumer Price Index measures the average change in prices paid by urban consumers for a basket of goods and services. The basket includes food and beverages (weighted most heavily at ~35%), housing, clothing, healthcare, transportation, education, and recreation. The base year is 2015-16. A CPI reading of 200 means prices have doubled since the base year.' },
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'How has inflation affected purchasing power in Pakistan since 2015?',
        acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'From 2015 to 2026, cumulative inflation in Pakistan has eroded roughly 60-70% of the PKR\'s purchasing power. PKR 100 in 2015 is worth approximately PKR 35-40 in real terms in 2026. This was driven by persistent fiscal deficits, currency depreciations, energy price reforms, and the 2022-23 balance-of-payments crisis. Use the calculator above to see the impact on any specific amount.' },
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'Which investments beat inflation in Pakistan?',
        acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Historically, gold and real estate have broadly kept pace with PKR inflation. National Savings certificates (Behbood at 13.68%, RIC at 13.56% in 2026) currently offer returns well above current inflation of under 1%, making them attractive in real terms. Equities (PSX-100) have also outperformed inflation over long periods. Use the National Savings Calculator and Gold Calculator on HisaabKar.pk to compare.' },
      },
    ],
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">

    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <nav class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-green-700">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-1">/</span>
      <a href="/tools" class="hover:text-green-700">Tools</a>
      <span class="mx-1">/</span>
      <span>Inflation Calculator</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">{title}</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6 text-sm">
      Enter an amount to see how much it would be worth in today's rupees after accounting for inflation.
      Data from Pakistan Bureau of Statistics (PBS) Consumer Price Index.
    </p>

    <InflationCalculator client:load />

    <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg text-xs text-amber-800">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> CPI figures are sourced from PBS and represent national urban averages.
      Individual purchasing power may differ based on consumption basket, region, and income group.
      2026 figure is an estimate based on latest available monthly data.
      Source: <a href="https://www.pbs.gov.pk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline">Pakistan Bureau of Statistics</a>.
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ / SEO content -->
    <div class="mt-12 prose prose-sm max-w-none text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-3">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mt-5 mb-2">What is Pakistan's inflation rate in 2026?</h3>
      <p>CPI inflation has fallen to approximately 0.3–0.7% YoY in early 2026 — the lowest in years — down from a peak of 38% in May 2023. Cumulative price levels since 2020 remain very high despite the low current rate.</p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mt-5 mb-2">What does PBS CPI measure?</h3>
      <p>The Consumer Price Index tracks price changes for an urban household's basket of goods: food (~35% weight), housing, clothing, healthcare, transport, and education. Base year is 2015-16. CPI of 200 means prices doubled since 2015.</p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mt-5 mb-2">How much has inflation eroded PKR purchasing power since 2015?</h3>
      <p>Approximately 60–70% of purchasing power lost. PKR 100 in 2015 buys what PKR 35–40 buys in 2026. This reflects successive depreciations, energy price reforms, and the 2022–23 balance-of-payments crisis.</p>

      <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mt-5 mb-2">Which investments beat inflation in Pakistan?</h3>
      <p>Gold and real estate have broadly tracked PKR inflation. National Savings certificates (Behbood: 13.68%, RIC: 13.56% in 2026) offer returns far above current ~1% inflation, making them exceptionally attractive in real terms right now.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
